Atletico Madrid on Wednesday night defeated Liverpool to reach the Champions League quarter-finals. Marcos Llorente’s extra-time double helped Atletico Madrid grab a 3-2 win over Liverpool and 4-2 victory on aggregate. According to football stats, Liverpool have fallen at the last 16 stage of the Champions League for the first time since 2006 (v Benfica), also as the reigning champions after lifting the trophy in 2005 at this season’s final destination – Istanbul.